<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-02-16T01:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-02-16T01:00:00-05:00" n="72" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d72">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">611.4731/454: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Australia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Canberra</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-02-16T17:00:00+11:00">February 16, 1943—5 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received February 16—4:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>33. My 32, February 16.<note n="2" xml:id="d72fn2">Not printed; it
                                    reported information from the Minister of Customs, H. V. Keane,
                                    that the Australian Government would grant most-favored-nation
                                    treatment to American goods by proclamation by the Governor
                                    General, which would become effective within 24 hours of its
                                    issuance (611.4731/453).</note> Effective date postponed one day
                                in order to enable Customs Minister, who is a Senator, to make a
                                statement in the Senate tomorrow simultaneous with statement in the
                                House, Senate not sitting today. We have vainly suggested that
                                publicity might be undesirable.</p>
                            <p>Text of statement being sent in my 34 of today.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>